  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/career-corner/my-most-clever-response-in-a-job-interview/cns-p/13758025</id>
    <title>My Most Clever Response in a Job Interview</title>
    <updated>2024-07-11T12:50:10.231000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>TammyPowlas</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/82</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Many moons ago, one of my managers gave me this great piece of advice.&amp;nbsp; He told me at any job interview, when they ask you at the end of the interview, "do you have any final questions" you ask this:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Is there anything about me or my background that wouldn't make me a good fit for this job?&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;After asking that, I have always received a job offer&amp;nbsp;&lt;EM&gt;except&lt;/EM&gt; one time.&amp;nbsp; It's a great question, and I hope you use it successfully like I did.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/career-corner/my-most-clever-response-in-a-job-interview/cns-p/13758025"/>
    <published>2024-07-11T12:50:10.231000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
