  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/career-corner-discussions/most-demanding-modules-in-sap/m-p/13759156#M15943</id>
    <title>Re: Most demanding modules in SAP</title>
    <updated>2024-07-12T12:50:43.231000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>TammyPowlas</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/82</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;I think that depends on your background and point of view.&amp;nbsp; For example, if you don't have a background in Finance or Accounting, but are responsible for the formerly known "FICO" modules, that could be demanding for you, whereas an accountant should have an easier time with it.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;That said, I would start with a background in project management&amp;nbsp;&lt;A href="https://learning.sap.com/courses/sap-activate" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;https://learning.sap.com/courses/sap-activate&lt;/A&gt;&amp;nbsp;- not that everyone is a project manager, but it gives an overview of projects and how they will flow.&amp;nbsp; Usually everyone is a team member at some point in time.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/career-corner-discussions/most-demanding-modules-in-sap/m-p/13759156#M15943"/>
    <published>2024-07-12T12:50:43.231000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
